SOLD: I am offering a hand-picked un-used after arsenal refurbishment Yugoslavian 59/66 SKS with the grenade launcher sights and attachment. This rifle is in excellent condition and the cold hammer forged barrel is new. It comes complete with the rifle's original log book, military issue leather ammo pouches, cleaning kit that resides in the buttstock and the brass oil decanter w/ leather carrying pouch. Importantly, I had Murray's Gunsmithing install their best SS firing pin which includes reaming the firing pin shaft and re-facing the bolt. This firing pin is much better than the stock Yugo SKS firing pin and it eliminates the potential SKS problem of the firing pin sticking in the strike position which can make the rifle go uncontrollably automatic emptying out your magazine. That cost me $70.00. I also bought a flash hider to replace the grenade launcher nozzle. Lastly, I bought a leather SKS rifle sling Of course I kept the original grenade launcher nozzle as well as the original firing pin and both will be included with the rifle.I have $600 in this rifle not to mention the waiting for a month to get the firing pin installed bolt back from Murray's Gunsmithing and then there is the dirty deed of cleaning all of the cosmoline out of every nook and cranny! That took hours! You can get a Yugo SKS for less than this but you can't get a Yugo SKS with all of the improvements I have on this one for less. Also, I bought this from Classic Firearms back when they first got these in and I ordered it hand-picked with the guarantee of the inclusion original arsenal log. It is truly in near new condition. If you order an SKS from Classic now, it's a crapshoot as to what you will get. With this one you know what you are getting.
